1
00:00:00,458 --> 00:00:05,000
These are the suspension
spots, right here

2
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:09,708
And this is the interrogation
room, the interrogation room is here

3
00:00:11,625 --> 00:00:17,833
And here the <i>balingo</i> [hoist for suspension]
is in the ceiling, hanging from the ceiling

4
00:00:19,125 --> 00:00:23,625
And here there is a table with
batteries and an electrical panel

5
00:00:23,916 --> 00:00:30,708
Of course electric shock. They connect the electricity
to the handcuffs and shock you during interrogation

6
00:00:31,458 --> 00:00:37,833
The interrogators present numbered two or three. Of course
we could hear what seemed like recording inside the room

7
00:00:38,083 --> 00:00:44,125
They have cameras here, placed in the room, and
they even placed cameras in the solitary cells

8
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:50,083
Interviewer: What are the names
of the torture methods they used?

9
00:00:50,250 --> 00:00:55,708
For example, the hose they call
<i>Lakhdar Brahimi.</i> They use it for flogging

10
00:00:56,583 --> 00:01:03,416
Electric shock, and the common one is suspension,
and beating with a whip while you are suspended

11
00:01:04,041 --> 00:01:06,375
Interviewer: Is there anything
left on your body from the torture?

12
00:01:06,458 --> 00:01:12,541
Of course, here where the handcuffs
were, their marks are still on my hands

13
00:01:14,791 --> 00:01:20,916
The clasp went into my hand
because of how tightly they pressed it

14
00:01:20,958 --> 00:01:27,833
Of course this skin was protruding outward like
this. I spent three months with my hands trembling

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,250
Interviewer: How long did
the interrogation sessions last?

16
00:01:37,750 --> 00:01:44,208
One or two hours, and sometimes the
interrogation lasted four hours with beating

17
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:52,083
Suspension was sometimes three hours, sometimes two
hours, sometimes you stayed suspended for half an hour

18
00:01:52,875 --> 00:01:56,916
As for the beating, sometimes they
beat you for an hour along with suspension

19
00:02:00,375 --> 00:02:04,458
Interviewer: Did they
insult you or curse at you?

20
00:02:04,541 --> 00:02:11,708
Cursing or insulting, no. They
never cursed during interrogation

21
00:02:13,125 --> 00:02:16,083
They would say things like, you will
be executed. That was routine for them

22
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:23,333
Your execution is tomorrow or in a week. Get ready.
You will not leave here except for execution, and so on

23
00:02:24,666 --> 00:02:27,541
Interviewer: What scared you most
when you were taken to interrogation?

24
00:02:28,291 --> 00:02:33,791
I feared execution. I feared they
would say, you will be executed

25
00:02:34,291 --> 00:02:41,291
Every time they took us to interrogation we wondered, they
told us last time we would be executed, they will behead you

26
00:02:41,833 --> 00:02:49,041
So every time they took you to interrogation you felt like you were
being taken to your execution. They made you live with that feeling

27
00:02:50,416 --> 00:02:53,708
Interviewer: Did they take anyone
else with you for interrogation?

28
00:02:54,250 --> 00:03:00,791
No, we only heard their voices. They did not take two or
three at once, only one person at a time for interrogation

29
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:04,250
Interviewer: Do you know the names
or noms de guerre of the interrogators?

30
00:03:04,791 --> 00:03:12,791
Their noms de guerre, for example, they called the
interrogator Abu Usama. When we called him Abu Usama

31
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:18,583
He would say, I am not Abu Usama. Who told
you I am Abu Usama? They concealed their names

32
00:03:18,958 --> 00:03:23,791
The guard they called Abu
Safwan, from the Arabian Peninsula

33
00:03:24,083 --> 00:03:30,958
I asked him, are you Saudi? He scolded me and said,
I am not Saudi, I am from the Arabian Peninsula

34
00:03:33,541 --> 00:03:36,208
Interviewer: How did
the guards treat you?

35
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:43,833
As guards, their treatment was decent and they did
not bother us. If you asked for food they brought it

36
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:49,416
You call him, if you need medicine they bring it. That is it,
he has nothing to do with anything else and does not talk to us

37
00:03:50,125 --> 00:03:55,875
Unless you need something. You knock on the door and he
opens the small hatch. He is masked and wears all black

38
00:03:56,375 --> 00:04:00,791
You tell him what you want
and he gives it to you, he brings it

39
00:04:02,791 --> 00:04:05,958
Interviewer: Did any prisoner
get sick from the torture?

40
00:04:06,458 --> 00:04:09,916
Did they take any prisoner to a doctor? Or
did you ask for medicine and they brought it?

41
00:04:10,791 --> 00:04:17,750
As for medicine, we asked and they brought it. But
I never saw a sick prisoner taken out for treatment

42
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:23,041
Since you are with them here, if
you need medicine they bring it

43
00:04:25,416 --> 00:04:29,500
Cough syrup for example, or
anti-inflammatory pills, that is it

44
00:04:30,166 --> 00:04:36,958
If you had a heart condition or something similar, they brought your
medication, and whenever the prescription ran out they renewed it

45
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:40,541
Interviewer: What did
this place smell like?

46
00:04:40,583 --> 00:04:46,875
The smell of dampness of course. This place has a
strange smell. The ceiling has a damp smell, that is all

47
00:04:48,083 --> 00:04:53,291
And coughing was always widespread.
There were people coughing constantly

48
00:04:56,625 --> 00:04:58,750
That is it. It was summer
and the smell was damp

49
00:04:58,833 --> 00:05:06,708
Interviewer: After they tortured you, how
did they bring you back to the solitary cell?

50
00:05:06,750 --> 00:05:09,000
Interviewer: Describe
your condition for us

51
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:15,291
After the interrogator finishes with
you, you are blindfolded and handcuffed

52
00:05:15,625 --> 00:05:21,125
He leads you while you are handcuffed
along the wall, slowly, the guard walks you

53
00:05:21,666 --> 00:05:29,541
He takes you out walking along
the wall and leads you toward

54
00:05:30,291 --> 00:05:37,291
The solitary cell you were in, toward this door.
He returns you along the wall and tells you quietly

55
00:05:37,791 --> 00:05:44,500
At this point you are exhausted from the
interrogation and from the hoist, and he takes you

56
00:05:44,541 --> 00:05:51,708
Toward the solitary cell you were in,
returns you to it, and brings someone else

57
00:05:52,375 --> 00:05:59,916
He takes another person in
your place, toward the spot

58
00:06:00,458 --> 00:06:02,708
Toward the solitary cell, he
returns me to the solitary cell here

59
00:06:08,166 --> 00:06:14,333
Toward the solitary cell, he returns you to your
place, and you hear that he has taken someone else

60
00:06:15,416 --> 00:06:20,250
He takes someone else and interrogates them.
You hear only the screaming and beating

